events.1885: French in power on Tombo Island
events.1891: Conakry becomes capital of French colonial Riviéres du Sud
events.1893: Conakry becomes part of colonial French Guinea
events.1947: Franco-Guinean Union (political party) headquartered in city
events.1955: Catholic Metropolitan Archdiocese of Conakry established
events.1958: City becomes part of independent Guinea
events.1960: Camp Boiro concentration camp begins operating
events.1971: January: Hanging of government officials on 8 November Bridge
events.1973: 20 January: Assassination of Bissau-Guinean revolutionary Amílcar Cabral
events.1984: March: Funeral of Ahmed Sékou Touré
events.1991: City administration sectioned into 5 communes: Dixinn, Kaloum, Matam, Matoto, Ratoma
events.1992: Le Lynx satirical newspaper begins publication
events.2014: March: Conakry regional governor Sékou Resco Camara leaves office
events.2017: City named World Book Capital by UNESCO
